==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bromoform
<hw>Bro"mo*form</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Brom</ets>ine + <ets>form</ets>yl.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless liquid, <chform>CHBr3</chform>, having an agreeable
odor and sweetish taste. It is produced by the simultaneous action of
bromine and caustic potash upon wood spirit, alcohol, or acetone, as
also by certain other reactions. In composition it is the same as
chloroform, with the substitution of bromine for chlorine. It is
somewhat similar to chloroform in its effects.</def>
<rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bromogelatin</ent>⟦br⟧
